This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category as it deals with the challenge of discovering and exploiting causal structure in the environment, which is a crucial aspect of intelligent agents. The use of meta-reinforcement learning to achieve causal reasoning also falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 

The cs.LG sub-category is also likely as the paper involves training a recurrent neural network with reinforcement learning, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

The cs.CL sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with language understanding and interpretation, which is relevant to natural language processing. 

The cs.RO sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses strategies for structured exploration in reinforcement learning, which is relevant to robotics. 

Finally, the cs.SY sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with the design and control of complex systems, which is relevant to systems and control theory.
